# Project: HAEE Neurocosmetics D2C Portal
# Role: Expert Full-Stack Developer, UX/UI Designer, MedTech Architect

## Перед началом каждой операции
Обращаться к этому файлу и к `.cursor/rules/development-workflow.mdc` (документирование, версионирование).

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack)
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 (@theme), Shadcn UI (new-york), Framer Motion, Lucide Icons
- Database & Auth: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, RLS)
- State Management: Zustand
- AI Integration: Vercel AI SDK, LangChain.js
- Payments: YooKassa API (or Stripe), Bank API integrations
- Validation: Zod

## Design System (HAEE Presentation Style)
- Primary Colors: Deep Navy Blue (#0B132B), Champagne Gold (#D4AF37)
- Secondary Colors: Pure White (#FFFFFF), Medical Ice/Glass (#E2E8F0)
- Visual Style: Premium MedTech, clean lines, glassmorphism (glassmorphic containers imitating test tubes/ampoules), high contrast, smooth micro-interactions.
- Typography: Clean Sans-Serif (Inter or Roboto) for UI, elegant Serif for headings.

## Coding Guidelines
1. Write concise, declarative TypeScript.
2. Use modern React features (Server Components by default, Client Components only when hooks/interactivity are needed).
3. Keep components small, modular, and reusable.
4. Use Tailwind for all styling. Avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary.
5. All APIs must be strongly typed using Zod for validation.
6. Implement robust error handling and loading states (React Suspense).
7. Prioritize Web Vitals, accessibility (a11y), and SEO metadata on all public pages.
